backgroundOptimisation_manager¶

Data¶

str TOOL_NAMESPACE

str TOOL_NAME

Functions¶

def install()

def uninstall()

Description¶

Manage installation of the Background Optimisation Manager to a Node Editor editor within the current Maya session.

The Background Optimisation Manager optimises the background rendering for each PySide2.QtWidgets.QGraphicsView of a Node Editor. Specifically it toggles background caching at a specific scaling (zoom) threshold.

The msTools.tools.tool_manager can be used to retrieve existing Background Optimisation Managers using the TOOL_NAMESPACE and TOOL_NAME.

msTools.tools.nodeEditorExtensions.backgroundOptimisation_manager.TOOL_NAMESPACE = 'MRS:Node Editor'¶

The tool namespace used to register a Background Optimisation Manager with the msTools.tools.tool_manager.

Type:str
msTools.tools.nodeEditorExtensions.backgroundOptimisation_manager.TOOL_NAME = 'Background Optimisation Manager'¶

The tool name used to register a Background Optimisation Manager with the msTools.tools.tool_manager.

Type:str
msTools.tools.nodeEditorExtensions.backgroundOptimisation_manager.install(parent, force=False)¶

Install the Background Optimisation Manager to a given Node Editor editor widget.

The tool will be registered with the msTools.tools.tool_manager.

Parameters:
  • parent (PySide2.QtWidgets.QTabWidget) – A Node Editor editor, to be used as the parent for the Background Optimisation Manager.
  • force (bool) – Whether to reinstall the Background Optimisation Manager if one already exists under parent. If False, skip installation if a Background Optimisation Manager already exists under parent. Defaults to False.
Raises:

msTools.coreUI.maya.exceptions.MayaUITypeError – If parent is not a Node Editor editor.
Returns:

The Background Optimisation Manager tool parented under parent. If force is False, this could be an existing tool.
msTools.tools.nodeEditorExtensions.backgroundOptimisation_manager.uninstall(tool)¶

Uninstall a given Background Optimisation Manager.

The tool will be deregistered from the msTools.tools.tool_manager.

Parameters:tool – A Background Optimisation Manager tool to uninstall.
